cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.NE, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.GT (Game Theory): The paper presents a framework to model strategic aspects and resource allocations in networks via coalitional games. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper presents polynomial-time algorithms to compute and verify least core payoffs of cost-based generalizations of path coalitional games and their duals. 
3. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper deals with graph theory and combinatorial optimization problems related to path coalitional games. 
4. cs.NE (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses resource allocations in networks and how coalitional games can be used to model them. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper presents algorithms for computing the least core payoffs and nucleolus of path coalitional games, which are relevant to AI research on cooperative game theory.
